                <h1>The Evolution of Google: From Search Engine to Tech Giant</h1>
                <p>Google was founded in 1998 by Larry Page and Sergey Brin while they were Ph.D. students at Stanford University. Initially a search engine project called "Backrub," it quickly gained popularity due to its innovative PageRank algorithm. Over the years, Google expanded its services with Gmail, Google Maps, and Android, becoming a global tech leader.</p>
